<p>The Gospel for this month is <a href="http://www.yfc.org.nz/private/bible/book.asp?book=john">John</a>. We have heard from a few people that they are particularly enjoying the <a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John%201%20;&version=65;">Message</a> version of the Gospels. Some are even reading it in two versions to see the differences and what they reveal.</p>
<p>For those on mission bases you will know that Wednesday is the day for praying for the rest of the mission nationwide. We received an email from Scott in Wanganui which is excellent and creative. It is at the bottom of this update.</p>
<p>YFCNZ is also actively involved in the Pacific development with Sereki (<a href="http://www.yfcfiji.org">Fiji</a>) and Isaia (Samoa). Some good news is that Bento has been with Sereki training for the past few years and is now planning to go home to Kiribati to start YFC and both Sereki and Isaia are visiting Vanuatu this month to plan a work there. It&rsquo;s all exciting particularly as it is being led by locals.</p>
<p>Planning for <a href="http://www.canvas.org.nz">Canvas</a>, Southern Harvest and <a href="http://www.summerharvest.co.nz">Summer Harvest</a> are all underway. Make sure you all have the information you need to be involved and to get kids involved. These opportunities are too good for young people too miss out on.</p>
<p>And finally&hellip;.be encouraged. We are getting there!</p>
